# strucmod — Cursor entry

This project uses the **strucmod** pipeline. The canonical instruction
source is `AGENTS.md` at the project root, which points at the plugin's
`skills/`, `agents/`, and `rules/` directories.

## Mandatory reading on every Cursor session

1. `AGENTS.md` (project root)
2. `<plugin-root>/skills/strucmod/SKILL.md`
3. `<plugin-root>/rules/orchestrator-protocol.md`
4. `<plugin-root>/rules/plan-first-modeling.md`
5. `<plugin-root>/rules/academic-writing-style.md`

`<plugin-root>` is typically `.claude/plugins/strucmod/` (project install) or `~/.claude/plugins/strucmod/` (user install).

## When the user asks Cursor to do anything related to:

- DSGE / CGE / heterogeneous-agent / dynamic programming — invoke the corresponding `setup-*` skill defined in `<plugin-root>/skills/setup-*/SKILL.md`.
- Solving a model — first run `validate-steady-state`, then `solve-perturbation` / `solve-vfi`.
- Reporting any numerical result — require `verifier` review before writing to manuscript.
- Writing a paper section — invoke the corresponding `write-*` skill and submit to `paper-reviewer` for academic-style review.

## Hard constraints

- Never write parameter values without a source recorded in `code/01_calibration.csv`.
- Never invoke a solver without `model-reviewer` approval.
- Never modify `code/seed.txt`, `.gitignore`, or `paper/main.tex` casually.
- All manuscript prose follows `<plugin-root>/rules/academic-writing-style.md` — no file paths, no pipeline talk, no bash commands in body.
- Use relative paths; code comments default to Chinese; manuscript prose in English.
